org.knime.core.node

Class ExtendedScopeNodeModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.NodeModel
      • org.knime.core.node.ExtendedScopeNodeModel
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    VirtualSubNodeInputNodeModel, VirtualSubNodeOutputNodeModel

    public abstract class ExtendedScopeNodeModel
extends NodeModel
    (No-API) Core Extension of NodeModel that widens the scope of some of the methods. It's used internally by certain system nodes like the subnode internal start/end nodes to have more control. For instance, they allow the node model implementation to set the entire node inactive.
    Since:
    2.11
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switerzerland
    No public API: not to be extended by clients
    This class is not intended to be subclassed nor used by clients.

    • Method Detail

      • executeModel

        protected PortObject[] executeModel(PortObject[] rawData,
                                    ExecutionEnvironment exEnv,
                                    ExecutionContext exec)
                             throws Exception
        Widens scope to protected. Invokes the abstract #execute() method of this model. In addition, this method notifies all assigned views of the model about the changes.
        Overrides:
        executeModel in class NodeModel
        Parameters:
        rawData - An array of PortObject objects holding the data from the inputs (includes flow variable port).
        exEnv - The execution environment used for execution of this model.
        exec - The execution monitor which is passed to the execute method of this model.
        Returns:
        The result of the execution in form of an array with DataTable elements, as many as the node has outputs.
        Throws:
        Exception - any exception or error that is fired in the derived model will be just forwarded. It may throw an CanceledExecutionException if the user pressed cancel during execution. Even if the derived model doesn't check, the result will be discarded and the exception thrown.
        IllegalStateException - If the number of PortObject objects returned by the derived NodeModel does not match the number of outputs. Or if any of them is null.
        See Also:
        NodeModel.execute(PortObject[],ExecutionContext)
